Rationale: every task — natural-language prompt, reference solution, buggy
solution, scenarios, and the mock APIs they exercise — is original work authored
for this benchmark. No third-party source code, repository content, or contest
problem text is redistributed. This keeps the benchmark free of upstream license
obligations (GPL/AGPL propagation, share-alike, non-commercial clauses) and free
of training-data contamination by construction: the mock APIs did not exist
before publication, so no model can have memorized their usage.
